# General Mobile App Testing Checklist

## 1. Installation and Launch
- [ ] The app installs successfully from the App Store / Google Play
- [ ] The app launches successfully after installation
- [ ] The app icon is displayed correctly on the home screen

## 2. Registration / Login
- [ ] A new user can be registered successfully
- [ ] Email and password validation works correctly
- [ ] Login is successful with valid credentials
- [ ] An error message is displayed when an incorrect password is entered

## 3. Core Functionality
- [ ] A new item (habit / task) can be created
- [ ] An existing item can be edited
- [ ] An existing item can be deleted
- [ ] Reminder settings work correctly (add / edit / delete)

## 4. Navigation and UI
- [ ] All screens open without freezing
- [ ] Buttons are clickable and perform the expected action
- [ ] Icons and text are displayed clearly
- [ ] Screen rotation works correctly

## 5. Notifications
- [ ] Push reminders are received at the scheduled time
- [ ] Tapping a push notification opens the correct screen

## 6. Profile and Settings
- [ ] Profile editing works correctly
- [ ] Logout is completed successfully
- [ ] Saved settings are applied correctly

## 7. Connectivity and Error Handling
- [ ] A message is shown when there is no internet connection
- [ ] A loading indicator is displayed when the internet connection is slow
- [ ] Server errors are handled with an appropriate message

## 8. Additional Checks
- [ ] The app does not crash during standard actions
- [ ] Battery consumption is within an acceptable range
- [ ] Permission requests are displayed correctly
